    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-09-15T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-09-15T17:00:00-05:00" n="373"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d373">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C1199/225: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="15" xml:id="d373fn15">The same on the same date to the
                        Ambassador in France as Department’s No. 349.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-15T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 15, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>338. Please secure promptly a copy of the report of the League Economic Committee
                    which has just been released. It deals with various aspects of commercial policy
                    including the most-favored-nation question. In main substance it appears to be a
                    highly satisfactory support for the program which the Department has been
                    advancing and for which it has sought the concerted initiative of other
                    governments.</p>
                <p>Also before the Assembly meeting, will you see the proper officials of the
                    Government and query them as to what instructions will be given as to the
                    disposition of the report by the Council and Assembly. You may freely make known
                    our reaction to the report and our interest that it should not remain an
                    ineffectual analysis and statement of recommendation and that everything
                    feasible should be done by all interested governments to develop action in
                    accord with it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
